President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation declaring June 2018 as African-American Music Appreciation Month. The proclamation recognizes the achievements and contributions of African-American musicians throughout history and celebrates the various genres of music they have created, such as rock and roll, rhythm and blues, jazz, gospel, hip hop, and rap. The proclamation emphasizes the power of African-American music to elicit emotions, unite people of all backgrounds, and serve as a voice for freedom, justice, love, and the pursuit of happiness. It also acknowledges the impact of African-American musicians in shaping the American dream and instilling a sense of pride in being American. The proclamation calls upon public officials, educators, and all people in the United States to observe the month with activities and programs that raise awareness and appreciation of African-American music.